I had a craving for Indian food for days. I looked up local Indian restaurants and found Shaahi Biryani. The following is my honest review. I ordered palak paneer, samosas, vegetable biryani and partha. When I got my order it came with yogurt sauce and tamarind chutney.  So good. The staff was very friendly and welcoming. Huge plus. Now the food. The one item I was looking forward to the most was the samosas. I was very disappointed because they were cold. I'm not sure if this is how they are served at this particular restaurant, but I was definitely not loving it. The palak paneer was good. Paneer is one of my favorite dishes. Huge cheese lover here. The partha was a good combination to eat the paneer with. This was my first time trying partha. I definitely enjoyed it. The vegetable biryani took the cake. I am loving the fragrance and taste of all the spices used to make it. It had chunks of potato and cauliflower. Yummmmm! The portion is ridiculously generous. I'd definitely go back to this restaurant if it weren't for the samosas. I'll have to shop around to other Indian restaurant to see where I can get them the way I like them.
